## 5. Definitions

"Commercial use"/"Commercial purpose" is defined as any use of the project or its parts with the intent of profit, including but not limited to selling, licensing, or using the project in a commercial product or service.
- Sharing the project in a youtube video or any other public and free-to-access media, even if monetized, is not considered a commercial use.
- Using the project in a free product with premium features or in a product that is sold is considered a commercial use, including but not limited to closed weight AI training.
- Using the project in a free product with donations is not considered a commercial use.
"Non-commercial purposes" is every use that is not a commercial use, including personal use, educational use, and research purposes.

A "contribution" is defined as any addition, modification, or improvement to the project, including but not limited to code, documentation, or other materials. The contribution can come in any form, including but not limited to pull requests, patches, or other forms of submission.

"Proper credits" are defined as giving credit to the original author(s) of the project and any contributors in a clear and visible manner, including their copyright notices, license information and links to the original project. Any additional credits is optional.
